# u-forge.ai — LLM Rules Entrypoint

This file is your routing guide. Before proceeding with any task in this project,
read the rule files listed under the matching section(s) below. Rule files live in
`.rulesdir/` and contain authoritative patterns, constraints, and context you must
follow.

---

## Always Read First

> **`.rulesdir/project-structure.mdc`**

Read this for every task. It covers the project's purpose, current architecture,
migration direction, module map, and the active known-bug list (BUG-1 through BUG-7).
Never make architectural decisions without it.

---

## Task-Based Routing

### Setting up the environment / running builds or tests
→ Read **`.rulesdir/environment-config.mdc`**
→ Read **`.rulesdir/development-workflow.mdc`**

Covers: `source env.sh` requirement, compiler variables (CC/CXX), environment
variable resolution order, build commands, Lemonade Server setup, and
cross-platform notes. You must source `env.sh` before any `cargo` command.

---

### Writing or modifying Rust source code (`src/*.rs`, `examples/*.rs`)
→ Read **`.rulesdir/rust-patterns.mdc`**

Covers: error handling with `anyhow`, the `EmbeddingProvider` trait (the central AI
abstraction — do NOT bypass it), the `ObjectBuilder` fluent API, string-based edge
types, RocksDB vs SQLite storage patterns, async anti-patterns (BUG-5), and
performance instrumentation.

---

### Adding, editing, or validating schema files (`defaults/schemas/*.schema.json`)
→ Read **`.rulesdir/schema-system.mdc`**
→ Read **`.rulesdir/json-data-formats.mdc`**

Covers: schema file format, the `add_` prefix convention and how `SchemaIngestion`
strips it, property types, validation rules, edge type schemas, and the 13 built-in
TTRPG types. Also covers how schemas relate to the JSONL import format.

---

### Working with data files (`defaults/data/*.json`) or the import pipeline
→ Read **`.rulesdir/json-data-formats.mdc`**

Covers: JSONL node and edge record format, supported `nodeType` values, the two-pass
import pipeline in `data_ingestion.rs`, and the active data bugs (BUG-6 deduplication,
BUG-7 in-session-only edge resolution).

---

### Writing, running, or debugging tests
→ Read **`.rulesdir/testing-debugging.mdc`**
→ Read **`.rulesdir/rust-patterns.mdc`** (testing patterns section)

Covers: isolated `TempDir`-based test setup, mock vs real `EmbeddingProvider`
selection, Lemonade integration test setup, regression test patterns for known bugs,
`RUST_LOG` levels, structured tracing, common symptom→cause→fix table, and CI
commands.

---

### Adding a new embedding provider or AI integration
→ Read **`.rulesdir/rust-patterns.mdc`** (EmbeddingProvider section)
→ Read **`.rulesdir/development-workflow.mdc`** (Adding a new EmbeddingProvider)
→ Read **`.rulesdir/environment-config.mdc`** (Lemonade Server Configuration)

New providers must implement the `EmbeddingProvider` trait. The Lemonade Server HTTP
provider is the target pattern. Do not use `Mutex<T>` in async embedding paths.

---

### Fixing a known bug (BUG-1 through BUG-7)
→ Read **`.rulesdir/project-structure.mdc`** (Known Bugs section)
→ Read **`.rulesdir/development-workflow.mdc`** (Bug fix workflow)
→ Read **`.rulesdir/testing-debugging.mdc`** (Known Bug Testing)

Always check `ARCHITECTURE.md` for the bug ID's full description and which migration
phase addresses it. Write a regression test before applying the fix.

---

### Planning or executing any migration phase work
→ Read **`.rulesdir/project-structure.mdc`** (Migration Direction)
→ Read **`.rulesdir/development-workflow.mdc`** (Architecture Context)
→ Read **`.rulesdir/environment-config.mdc`** (Planned Configuration)

Migration phases: (1) Lemonade embeddings, (2) SQLite + sqlite-vec + FTS5,
(3) axum HTTP/WebSocket server, (4) reranking, (5) Cargo workspace split.
Never implement a phase out of order without explicit instruction.

---

## Quick Reference: File → Topic

| File | Primary Topics |
|---|---|
| `project-structure.mdc` | Architecture, module map, migration direction, known bugs |
| `development-workflow.mdc` | Build/run commands, adding providers/schemas, bug workflow |
| `environment-config.mdc` | `env.sh`, env vars, path resolution, Lemonade setup |
| `rust-patterns.mdc` | Error handling, traits, storage, async, ObjectBuilder |
| `schema-system.mdc` | Schema format, validation, property types, edge schemas |
| `json-data-formats.mdc` | JSONL node/edge format, import pipeline, data bugs |
| `testing-debugging.mdc` | Test setup, mocks, logging, CI commands, debug table |